### **üîß Module Interfaces Design:**

#### **1. StateManager.js**
```javascript
class StateManager {
    constructor() {
        this.state = {
            character: {},
            ui: {},
            form: {}
        };
        this.listeners = new Map();
    }

    // Public API
    getState(path) { }
    setState(path, value) { }
    subscribe(path, callback) { }
    unsubscribe(path, callback) { }
    reset() { }
}
```

#### **2. EventManager.js**
```javascript
class EventManager {
    constructor() {
        this.delegatedEvents = new Map();
    }

    // Public API
    delegate(selector, event, handler) { }
    removeDelegation(selector, event) { }
    emit(eventName, data) { }
    on(eventName, handler) { }
    off(eventName, handler) { }
}
```

#### **3. TabManager.js**
```javascript
class TabManager {
    constructor(stateManager, eventManager) {
        this.state = stateManager;
        this.events = eventManager;
    }

    // Public API
    switchTab(tabIndex) { }
    updateProgress(tabIndex) { }
    setSheetMode(mode) { }
    getCurrentTab() { }
    validateTab(tabIndex) { }
}
```

#### **4. PreviewManager.js**
```javascript
class PreviewManager {
    constructor(stateManager, eventManager) {
        this.state = stateManager;
        this.events = eventManager;
        this.cache = new Map();
    }

    // Public API
    updatePreview() { }
    updateBasicInfo() { }
    updateTraits() { }
    updateAbilities() { }
    updateDisciplines() { }
    clearCache() { }
}
```

### **üîÑ Communication Patterns:**

#### **State Management Strategy:**
- **Centralized State:** Single source of truth in StateManager
- **Reactive Updates:** Components subscribe to state changes
- **Immutable Updates:** State changes create new objects
- **Validation Layer:** All state changes go through validation

#### **Event System:**
- **Event Delegation:** Single event listener per event type
- **Custom Events:** Component communication via custom events
- **Event Bubbling:** Natural DOM event flow
- **Error Events:** Centralized error handling

#### **Module Dependencies:**
```
StateManager (Core)
    ‚Üë
EventManager (Core)
    ‚Üë
TabManager, PreviewManager, UIManager (UI)
    ‚Üë
TraitSystem, AbilitySystem, DisciplineSystem (Systems)
    ‚Üë
DOMUtils, ValidationUtils, DataUtils (Utils)
```

### **‚ö° Performance Optimizations:**

#### **1. Debouncing Strategy:**
```javascript
// Input handlers - 300ms delay
const debouncedPreviewUpdate = debounce(updatePreview, 300);

// API calls - 500ms delay
const debouncedSave = debounce(saveCharacter, 500);
```

#### **2. DOM Caching:**
```javascript
class DOMCache {
    constructor() {
        this.cache = new Map();
    }

    get(selector) {
        if (!this.cache.has(selector)) {
            this.cache.set(selector, document.querySelector(selector));
        }
        return this.cache.get(selector);
    }
}
```

#### **3. Event Delegation:**
```javascript
// Single listener for all trait buttons
eventManager.delegate('.trait-btn', 'click', (e) => {
    const category = e.target.dataset.category;
    const traitName = e.target.dataset.traitName;
    traitSystem.selectTrait(category, traitName);
});
```

### **üõ°Ô∏è Error Handling Strategy:**

#### **1. Module-Level Error Handling:**
```javascript
class BaseModule {
    constructor() {
        this.errorHandler = new ErrorHandler();
    }

    safeExecute(fn, context = this) {
        try {
            return fn.call(context);
        } catch (error) {
            this.errorHandler.handle(error, context);
        }
    }
}
```

#### **2. Global Error Handler:**
```javascript
class ErrorHandler {
    handle(error, context) {
        console.error(`Error in ${context.constructor.name}:`, error);
        this.showUserError(error);
        this.reportError(error, context);
    }
}
```

